ocean_sigma_z.z_factors: sigma: sigma eta: eta depth: depth depth_c: depth_c nsigma: nsigma zlev: zlev
ocean_sigma_z.z_bounds_factors: sigma: sigma_bnds eta: eta depth: depth depth_c: depth_c nsigma: nsigma zlev: zlev_bnds
ocean_sigma_z.formula: for k <= nsigma: z(n,k,j,i) = eta(n,j,i) + sigma(k)*(min(depth_c,depth(j,i))+eta(n,j,i)) ; for k > nsigma: z(n,k,j,i) = zlev(k)

smooth_level.z_factors: a: a b1: b1 b2: b2 ztop: ztop zsurf1: zsurf1 zsurf2: zsurf2
smooth_level.z_bounds_factors: a: a_bnds b1: b1_bnds b2: b2_bnds ztop: ztop zsurf1: zsurf1 zsurf2: zsurf2

ocean_sigma.z_factors: sigma: lev eta: eta depth: depth
ocean_sigma.z_bounds_factors: sigma: lev_bnds eta: eta depth: depth

ocean_s.z_factors: s: lev eta: eta depth: depth a: a_coeff b: b_coeff depth_c: depth_c
ocean_s.z_bounds_factors: s: lev_bnds eta: eta depth: depth a: a b: b depth_c: depth_c
ocean_s.formula: z(n,k,j,i) = eta(n,j,i)*(1+s(k)) + depth_c*s(k) + (depth(j,i)-depth_c)*C(k) n where n C(k)=(1-b)*sinh(a*s(k))/sinh(a) +n           b*(tanh(a*(s(k)+0.5))/(2*tanh(0.5*a)) - 0.5)

alternate_hybrid_sigma.z_factors: ap: ap b: b ps: ps
alternate_hybrid_sigma.z_bounds_factors: ap: ap_bnds b: b_bnds ps: ps

time3.long_name: Diurnal cycle: monthly mean of the diurnal cycle (1 hour steps).

dbze.long_name: CloudSat simulator equivalent radar reflectivity factor

standard_sigma.z_factors: ptop: ptop sigma: lev ps: ps
standard_sigma.z_bounds_factors: ptop: ptop sigma: lev_bnds ps: ps

hybrid_height.z_factors: a: lev b: b orog: orog
hybrid_height.z_bounds_factors: a: lev_bnds b: b_bnds orog: orog

ocean_double_sigma.z_factors: sigma: sigma depth: depth z1: z1 z2: z2 a: a_coeff href: href k_c: k_c
ocean_double_sigma.z_bounds_factors: sigma: sigma_bnds depth: depth z1: z1 z2: z2 a: a href: href k_c: k_c
ocean_double_sigma.formula: for k <= k_c:n z(k,j,i)= sigma(k)*f(j,i) n for k > k_c:n z(k,j,i)= f(j,i) + (sigma(k)-1)*(depth(j,i)-f(j,i)) n f(j,i)= 0.5*(z1+ z2) + 0.5*(z1-z2)* tanh(2*a/(z1-z2)*(depth(j,i)-href))

standard_hybrid_sigma.z_factors: p0: p0 a: a b: b ps: ps
standard_hybrid_sigma.z_bounds_factors: p0: p0 a: a_bnds b: b_bnds ps: ps

rsds.comment: surface solar irradiance for UV calculations

prc.comment: Convective precipitation at surface; includes both liquid and solid phases.

prsn.comment: at surface; includes precipitation of all forms of water in the solid phase

rhsmin.comment: Surface daily minimum of relative humidity with respect to liquid water for T> 0 C, and with respect to ice for T<0 C.

vsi.comment: 'Reported as ''missing'' in regions free of sea ice.'

tslsi.comment: 'skin' temperature of all surfaces except open ocean.
tslsi.long_name: Surface Temperature Where Land or Sea Ice

pr.comment: includes both liquid and solid phases

sit.comment: the mean thickness of sea ice in the ocean portion of the grid cell (averaging over the entire ocean portion, including the ice-free fraction).  Reported as 0.0 in regions free of sea ice.
sit.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where sea

usi.comment: 'Reported as ''missing'' in regions free of sea ice.'

sic.comment: fraction of grid cell covered by sea ice.

mrsos.comment: The mass of water in all phases in the upper 10cm of the  soil layer.
mrsos.long_name: Moisture in Upper Portion of Soil Column
mrsos.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where land

vas.comment: Northward component of the near surface wind

uas.comment: Eastward component of the near-surface (usually, 10 meters)  wind

snc.comment: Fraction of each grid cell that is occupied by snow that rests on land portion of cell.

rlut.comment: at the top of the atmosphere (to be compared with satellite measurements)

rhs.comment: This is the relative humidity with respect to liquid water for T> 0 C, and with respect to ice for T<0 C.

rhsmax.comment: Surface daily maximum of relative humidity with respect to liquid water for T> 0 C, and with respect to ice for T<0 C.

omldamax.long_name: Daily Maximum Ocean Mixed Layer Thickness Defined by Mixing Scheme

hur.comment: The relative humidity with respect to liquid water for T> 0 C, and with respect to ice for T<0 C.

p0.long_name: vertical coordinate formula term: reference pressure

snw.comment: The mass of surface snow on the land portion of the grid cell divided by the land area in the grid cell; reported as missing where the land fraction is 0; excludes snow on vegetation canopy or on sea ice.
snw.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where land

sfcWindmax.comment: Daily maximum near-surface (usually, 10 meters) wind speed.

mrro.comment: The total run-off (including drainage through the base of the soil model) per unit area leaving the land portion of the grid cell.
mrro.cell_measures: time: mean area: mean where land

tossq.comment: square of temperature of liquid ocean, averaged over the day.

depth.long_name: Sea Floor Depth: formula term: thetao

eta.long_name: Sea Surface Height formula term: thetao

tasmin.comment: minimum near-surface (usually, 2 meter) air temperature (add cell_method attribute 'time: min')

tos.comment: this may differ from 'surface temperature' in regions of sea ice.

tasmax.comment: maximum near-surface (usually, 2 meter) air temperature (add cell_method attribute 'time: max')

wap.comment: Omega (vertical velocity in pressure coordinates, positive downwards)
